THREE trucks and seven cars reportedly were involved in a horror accident yesterday evening near the Pavillion Shopping Centre on the N3 East going towards Durban. Netcare 911 spokesperson Shawn Herbst said when they arrived at the scene, they found one man was seriously injured and needed advanced life support to stabilise him and another patient had moderate injuries and was treated on the scene. “There were 10 patients injured in the accident. Five needed advanced life support and one patient was placed on a manual ventilator. All the patients were transported to various hospitals,” said Herbst. Here's the accident that happened 3 hours ago in the n3 near pavilion 20 cars involved plz check on ur loved ones???? pic.twitter.com/XSPonzOHsp 